CONVEY.Definition: to express a thought or meaning

DECLINE.Definition: to decrease, to become worse and worse

DISDAIN.Definition: hatred, normally shown through a lack of respect

DIVERSE.Definition: including many different types of people or things:

DOMINANT.Definition: most important or strong than similar things

ENDANGER.Definition: to put someone or something at risk of being hurt or harmed

ENDANGERED.Definition: put at risk of being hurt of harmed

FOR THE SAKE OF.Definition: in order to allow something to happen

FRESCO.Definition: a painting on a wall, painted when the paint is still fresh

MEANS.Definition: way, a method to do something

NON-CORE.Definition: not the main, not the normal

OUTLAWING.Definition: completely stop something by making it illegal

PRESERVED.Definition: saved from being destroyed or harmed

REVIVAL.Definition: becoming more popular and in use again

SETS US APART.Definition: makes us different from or better than other people or things

THEORETICAL.Definition: based on an idea, not the practical use (of something)

UTILITARIAN.Definition: not caring for anything other than usefulness or practicality
